msgstr "Karttopologi"

#. TRANS: Freeciv-web version of the help text.
#: server/settings.c:1563
msgid "Freeciv-web maps are always two-dimensional.\n"
msgstr "Freeciv-web-kartor är alltid tvådimensionella.\n"

#. TRANS: do not edit the ugly ASCII art
#: server/settings.c:1566
msgid ""
"Freeciv maps are always two-dimensional. Individual tiles may be rectangular or hexagonal, with either an overhead (\"classic\") or isometric alignment.\n"
"To play with a particular topology, clients will need a matching tileset.\n"
"Overhead rectangular:      Isometric rectangular:\n"
"      _________               /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\\n"
"     |_|_|_|_|_|             /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\n"
"     |_|_|_|_|_|             \\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\\n"
"     |_|_|_|_|_|             /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\n"
"                             \\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\n"
"Hex:                       Iso-hex:\n"
"  /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\               _   _   _   _   _\n"
"  | | | | | | |             / \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\\n"
"  \\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\             \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/\n"
"   | | | | | | |            / \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\\n"
"   \\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/             \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/\n"
msgstr ""
"Freeciv-kartor är alltid tvådimensionella. Enskilda rutor kan vara rektangulära eller hexagonala, med antingen klassisk orientering ovanifrån eller isometrisk orientering.\n"
"För att spela med en viss topologi behöver klienterna en matchande rutbildsuppsättning.\n"
"Klassisk rektangulär:        Isometrisk rektangulär:\n"
"      _________               /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\\n"
"     |_|_|_|_|_|             /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\n"
"     |_|_|_|_|_|             \\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\\n"
"     |_|_|_|_|_|             /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\n"
"                             \\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\n"
"Hexagonal:                 Isohexagonal:\n"
"  /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\               _   _   _   _   _\n"
"  | | | | | | |             / \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\\n"
"  \\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\             \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/\n"
"   | | | | | | |            / \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\\n"
"   \\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/             \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/ \\_/\n"

